summary: An Ordinance accepting a deed from Edwin W. Craven and Mary B. Craven, his wife, of Seattle, Washington, to the City of Seattle, dated the 13th day of June, 1907, to Lots Two (2) and Three (3) Block Nine (9); Lots Eight (8) and Nine (9) in Block Ten (10) of Craven's Division of Green Lake Addition for Park and Parkway purposes, all in the City of Seattle.
